'''Murcaily''' can be found in [[Tai Bwo Wannai]], right next to the gate to the [[hardwood grove]]. He is not visible until you have completed the [[Jungle Potion]] quest, although he will speak to you if you try to enter the grove without paying.

Players must speak to Murcaily to start the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup]] minigame. Entering the grove costs 100 [[trading sticks]].

Murcaily plays a significant part in [[My Arm's Big Adventure]] in learning how to grow [[goutweed]]. The troll chef [[Burntmeat]] discovered this when interrogating one of the [[Adventurer|ingredients]] in his stew.

The hardwood grove area has 9 [[teak]]s and 4 [[mahogany]] trees. The grove contains three level 5 [[snake]]s which can make [[Woodcutting]] for [[pures]] awkward. However, this does not affect the majority of players. There are four axes lying on the floor, two [[bronze axe|bronze]] and two [[iron axe|iron]], which are generally not useful for the players who use the grove for experience, as cutting teak or mahogany is well above the requirement for using a bronze or iron axe for Woodcutting.

